{
  "text": "Standardized imaging protocols for both anatomic and metabolic imaging of the brain are essential for reliable and accurate diagnoMultimodality Imaging of Neurodegenerative Processes: Part 2, Atypical Dementias P rogress in anatomic and metabolic imaging, as described in part 1 [CITATION_1] , has led to a multimodality approach for imaging patients with cognitive decline. Although the combination of Alzheimer disease (AD), frontotemporal dementia (FTD), vascular dementia, and dementia with Lewy bodies (DLB), which are discussed in part 1 [CITATION_2] , accounts for at least 85% of the degenerative dementias, the remainder is significant. These atypical degenerative dementias have varied clinical presentations, prognoses, and treatments. As a result, correct diagnosis is essential for proper patient care and education.",
  "correct_citation": {
